We, too, cling to our illusions of permanence, our distraction from the human needs around us, and a smug addiction to our sense of power, wealth, appearance. Can we learn the ancient lesson? \"Do justice, walk humbly, and love the Holy One.\" In these we find our true strength, faith renewed, and abiding hope."}
